**Pirates and Gold: Backward Induction.** 5 perfectly rational pirates (ranked 1=most senior). Senior pirate proposes a split of 100 coins. If $\geq50\%$ agree, split is adopted; otherwise proposer is thrown overboard. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item Backward induction: what do 2, 3, 4 pirates do?

\item What does Pirate 1 propose with 5 pirates?

\item Does the answer change with 200 coins or 1 coin?\end{enumerate}

**Clock Hands Overlap.** \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item How many times do the hands overlap in 24 hours?

\item What is the first overlap time after 12:00?

\item During the 1:00 hour, when do the hands overlap?\end{enumerate}
